    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Jackson Merrill** stands out as the most vital start, holding an elite score of 67.37. Despite a looming test against the high-velocity Luis Castillo, the combination of his presumed #2 spot in the order and a favorable platoon advantage provides high-floor production that we cannot afford to leave on the bench. Similarly, **Jacob Wilson** (62.77) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (61.04) represent the core of our output; **Jacob Wilson** benefits significantly from a favorable park factor and a manageable matchup against Leiter, while **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** maintains his reliable utility in the #3 hole, balancing out the tougher matchup against Sproat.\n\nThe most challenging decision today was leaving **Brady House** (47.22) on the bench. While his projection benefited from a strong platoon edge against Ashcraft, he ultimately missed the cut because the current depth of our starting MI and 3B slots\u2014specifically **Jacob Wilson** and **Josh Jung**\u2014offered higher daily efficiency scores. We remain cautious with **Gunnar Henderson** (47.79); while his talent is undeniable, he is a primary risk factor today due to a 44% rain probability in his matchup against the left-handed Parker Messick. His score is suppressed by both the weather risk and the platoon disadvantage, making him the most volatile asset in our active lineup. We will be monitoring the weather and confirmed lineups closely to determine if any late-scratch protections are needed for him or **Jackson Merrill**.",
